
{ Determining column names and data types of a table #information_schema-columns-datatypes

  The column names and their → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[data types] can be determined with the columns view in in
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/INFORMATION_SCHEMA:

  gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/schemas/INFORMATION_SCHEMA/columns/select-datatypes.sql||

  Apparently, an alternative way is to use the stored procedure `sp_columns`.

}
